---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import Header from '../components/Header.tsx'
import '../index.css'
---

<Layout title="About - PhyloGuessr">
  <div class="game">
    <Header client:load />
    <div class="about-page">
      <h2>About PhyloGuessr</h2>

      <h3>How it works</h3>
      <p>You're shown three organisms and asked: which two are most closely related? The "closest pair" is whichever two share the most recent common ancestor on the tree of life.</p>

      <h3>Data sources</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Phylogenetic relationships are determined using the <a href="https://tree.opentreeoflife.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open Tree of Life</a> synthetic tree, which combines published phylogenetic studies with taxonomic data to produce a comprehensive tree of life</li>
        <li>Species names and the species pool for random mode come from the <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/taxonomy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NCBI Taxonomy</a> database</li>
        <li>Organism images come from <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Wikipedia</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Why Open Tree of Life?</h3>
      <p>NCBI Taxonomy is a classification system, not a phylogeny — it sometimes can't resolve which of three species are most closely related (a "polytomy"). The Open Tree of Life synthesizes hundreds of published phylogenetic studies to produce a tree with better resolution. For example, NCBI places primates, colugos, and rodents as unresolved children of Euarchontoglires, while the Open Tree correctly groups colugos with primates in Primatomorpha.</p>

      <h3>Contribute</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Source code is on <a href="https://github.com/cmdcolin/phyloguessr" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a></li>
        <li>Want to add your own example trios? <a href="https://github.com/cmdcolin/phyloguessr/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open an issue</a> or submit a pull request!</li>
        <li>Found a bug or wrong answer? <a href="https://github.com/cmdcolin/phyloguessr/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Let us know on GitHub</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
